Basic Education Minister, Angie Motshekga, says she too is anxious about her grandchildren going back to school. JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga will hold a media briefing on Sunday on the readiness of other grades to return to school on Monday. She will also give an update on progress since the return of Grade 7's and 12's to school last month. READ: Only Grade 6, 11 and Grade R will return to school on Monday Initially, all grades were scheduled to return to school on Monday with the exception of Grades 4, 8 and 9. On Thursday, this was reduced to Grades R, 6 and 11 amid a surge in COVID-19 cases. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.